<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - INSTALL - MAINSHAFT AND AUXILIARY DRIVE
        GEAR ASSEMBLIES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="6">
        <title>MAINSHAFT AND AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLIES</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the auxiliary drive gear assembly from the mainshaft and rear bearing bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021j4">Figure 194</hotlnk>). Do not allow the mainshaft to move to the rear when
                removing the auxiliary drive gear.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021j4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021j4" filename="../figg13/G13021J4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 194. Auxiliary Drive Gear Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the reverse gear to the rear as far as possible, meshing the teeth of the gear with
                those of the reverse idler gears (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021j5">Figure 195</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021j5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021j5" filename="../figg13/G13021J5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 195. Mesh Teeth Of Gears</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the external splines of the spacer with the clutching teeth of the reverse gear and
                move the spacer forward on the mainshaft and into reverse gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021j6">Figure 196</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021j6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021j6" filename="../figg13/G13021J6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 196. Align External Splines</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reinstall the auxiliary drive gear assembly on the rear of the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021j7">Figure 197</hotlnk>). Use a flanged end driver and maul to seat the bearing in
                the case bore.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021j7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021j7" filename="../figg13/G13021J7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 197. Seat Bearing In Case Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the six bolt holes in the retainer with the tapped holes in the case and install the
                bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021j8">Figure 198</hotlnk>). Tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226; m) and
                lockwire the bolts in groups of three.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021j8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021j8" filename="../figg13/G13021J8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 198. Tighten Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the snap ring on the mainshaft snap ring groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021j9">Figure 199</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021j9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021j9" filename="../figg13/G13021J9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 199. Install Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
